## 🎨 Visual Design Principles

### 1. Visual Hierarchy (Importance → Size/Weight/Color)

**Typographic Scale:**
```
H1: 36-48px - Page titles (most important)
H2: 24-30px - Section titles
H3: 20-24px - Subsection titles
Body: 16px - Default (optimal readability)
Small: 14px - Captions, metadata
Tiny: 12px - Timestamps, labels (use sparingly)
```

**Weight Hierarchy:**
```
Bold (700) - Primary actions, active states
Semibold (600) - Headings, important text
Medium (500) - Subheadings
Regular (400) - Body text (default)
Light (300) - Deemphasized text (use sparingly)
```

**Color Hierarchy:**
```
High contrast - Primary content (black/white)
Medium contrast - Secondary content (gray-700/gray-300)
Low contrast - Tertiary content (gray-500)
Accent - Interactive elements (magenta, cyan)
```

**Example - Task Card:**
```tsx
<div className="p-4 bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 rounded-lg">
  {/* PRIMARY - Task title (bold, high contrast) */}
  <h3 className="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">
    Implement dark mode toggle
  </h3>

  {/* SECONDARY - Metadata (medium weight, medium contrast) */}
  <p className="text-sm font-medium text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mt-1">
    Due: Nov 15, 2025
  </p>

  {/* TERTIARY - Timestamp (regular weight, low contrast) */}
  <p className="text-xs text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 mt-2">
    Created 2 hours ago
  </p>
</div>
```

### 2. Gestalt Principles (How Users Perceive Groups)

**Proximity** - Items close together are perceived as related
```tsx
❌ BAD: Equal spacing between all items
<div className="space-y-4">
  <h2>Settings</h2>
  <Toggle />
  <h2>Advanced</h2>
  <Toggle />
</div>

✅ GOOD: Group related items with proximity
<div className="space-y-8">
  <div className="space-y-2">
    <h2>Settings</h2>
    <Toggle />
  </div>
  <div className="space-y-2">
    <h2>Advanced</h2>
    <Toggle />
  </div>
</div>
```

**Similarity** - Similar items are perceived as related
```tsx
✅ Use consistent styling for related elements
<div className="flex gap-2">
  {/* All action buttons same style */}
  <button className="btn-secondary">Edit</button>
  <button className="btn-secondary">Share</button>
  <button className="btn-secondary">Export</button>
  {/* Destructive action different style */}
  <button className="btn-danger">Delete</button>
</div>
```

**Closure** - Users mentally complete incomplete shapes
```tsx
✅ Use partial borders for elegance
<div className="border-l-4 border-magenta-700 pl-4">
  Important note
</div>
```

**Figure-Ground** - Separate foreground from background
```tsx
✅ Use elevation and contrast
<div className="relative">
  {/* Background (blurred overlay) */}
  <div className="fixed inset-0 bg-black/50 backdrop-blur-sm" />

  {/* Foreground (modal pops out) */}
  <div className="relative z-10 bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 rounded-2xl shadow-floating">
    Modal content
  </div>
</div>
```

**Common Region** - Items within boundaries are grouped
```tsx
✅ Use cards/containers to group
<div className="p-6 bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-800 rounded-xl">
  {/* All items within this card are related */}
  <h3>Account Settings</h3>
  <Input label="Email" />
  <Input label="Password" />
  <Button>Save</Button>
</div>
```

### 3. Contrast & Accessibility

**WCAG 2.2 AA Requirements:**
- Normal text: 4.5:1 contrast minimum
- Large text (18pt+): 3:1 contrast minimum
- UI components: 3:1 contrast minimum

**Contrast Ratios (Pre-calculated for Neuman Brain):**
```css
/* ✅ PASS AA & AAA */
#000000 (black) on #FFFFFF (white)     = 21:1
#E91E8C (magenta) on #FFFFFF (white)   = 6.2:1
#00C9FF (cyan) on #000000 (black)      = 8.1:1
#FFFFFF (white) on #E91E8C (magenta)   = 4.7:1

/* ⚠️ PASS AA (but not AAA) */
#64748B (slate-500) on #FFFFFF (white) = 4.6:1

/* ❌ FAIL - Do not use */
#FF7EC7 (magenta-300) on #FFFFFF       = 2.1:1
#7FE4FF (cyan-300) on #FFFFFF          = 1.8:1
```

**When to Use High Contrast:**
- Body text (always)
- Critical UI elements (buttons, inputs)
- Error messages
- Focus indicators

**When Lower Contrast is OK:**
- Disabled states
- Placeholder text
- Tertiary metadata (timestamps)

### 4. White Space (Negative Space)

**"White space is not wasted space - it's breathing room for the eye."**

**Spacing Scale (Neuman Brain - 4px base):**
```
4px  (space-1) - Tight spacing (icon + text)
8px  (space-2) - Compact elements
12px (space-3) - Form field spacing
16px (space-4) - Component padding
20px (space-5) - Section spacing
24px (space-6) - Card padding
32px (space-8) - Large gaps
48px (space-12) - Section dividers
```

**Macro White Space (Between Sections):**
```tsx
✅ GOOD: Generous spacing between major sections
<div className="space-y-12">
  <section>Content 1</section>
  <section>Content 2</section>
  <section>Content 3</section>
</div>
```

**Micro White Space (Within Components):**
```tsx
✅ GOOD: Tight spacing within related items
<div className="flex items-center gap-2">
  <Icon className="w-4 h-4" />
  <span>Label</span>
</div>
```

### 5. Alignment & Grid Systems

**Types of Alignment:**
- **Edge** - Align to left/right edges (most common)
- **Center** - Align to center (use for symmetry)
- **Baseline** - Align text baselines (mixed font sizes)

**Grid System:**
```tsx
✅ Use consistent grid (12-column or flex gap)
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
  <Widget />
  <Widget />
  <Widget />
</div>
```

