## 🎭 Interaction Design

### 1. Affordances (Visual Hints for Interaction)

**Buttons should look clickable:**
```tsx
✅ GOOD: Clear affordance
<button className="px-6 py-3 bg-magenta-700 text-white rounded-lg shadow-soft hover:shadow-glow-magenta hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all">
  Click Me
</button>

❌ BAD: No affordance
<div className="text-magenta-700" onClick={handler}>
  Click Me
</div>
```

**Interactive elements:**
- Cursor changes to `pointer` on hover
- Visual feedback on hover (color shift, lift, glow)
- Active state on click (pressed effect)
- Disabled state is visually distinct (opacity, grayscale)

### 2. Feedback (Immediate Response to User Actions)

**Types of Feedback:**

**Visual Feedback:**
```tsx
// Button press effect
<button className="active:scale-95 transition-transform">
  Click
</button>

// Loading state
<button disabled className="opacity-50 cursor-not-allowed">
  <Spinner className="animate-spin" />
  Loading...
</button>

// Success state
<button className="bg-success-500">
  <Check className="w-4 h-4" />
  Saved!
</button>
```

**Haptic Feedback (where supported):**
```tsx
const handleClick = () => {
  // Trigger haptic feedback on mobile
  if ('vibrate' in navigator) {
    navigator.vibrate(10); // 10ms subtle vibration
  }
  // ... handle click
};
```

**Toast Notifications:**
```tsx
// Success toast (auto-dismiss)
toast.success('Task created successfully', {
  duration: 3000,
  position: 'bottom-right',
});

// Error toast (persistent, user dismisses)
toast.error('Failed to save. Check your connection.', {
  duration: Infinity,
  action: { label: 'Retry', onClick: retry },
});
```

**Timing Rules:**
- Instant feedback: < 100ms (button press, hover)
- Expected wait: 1-3s (loading spinner)
- Unexpected wait: > 3s (progress bar with percentage)

### 3. State Transitions (Smooth Changes)

**Animation Principles (Disney's 12 Principles Applied to UI):**

**Ease In/Out:**
```css
/* Smooth acceleration/deceleration */
transition: all 300ms cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
```

**Follow Through:**
```tsx
// Modal opens → overlay fades in → content slides up
<motion.div
  initial={{ opacity: 0 }}
  animate={{ opacity: 1 }}
  transition={{ duration: 0.2 }}
>
  <motion.div
    initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 20 }}
    animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
    transition={{ duration: 0.3, delay: 0.1 }}
  >
    Modal content
  </motion.div>
</motion.div>
```

**Anticipation:**
```tsx
// Button shrinks slightly before action (like a spring)
<motion.button
  whileTap={{ scale: 0.95 }}
  whileHover={{ scale: 1.05 }}
  transition={{ type: "spring", stiffness: 400, damping: 17 }}
>
  Submit
</motion.button>
```

