## ♿ Accessibility & Inclusive Design

### 1. Beyond Compliance (WCAG 2.2 AA is the Floor, Not the Ceiling)

**Inclusive Design Principles:**
1. **Equitable** - Everyone gets equal access
2. **Flexible** - Works for diverse abilities
3. **Simple** - Easy to understand
4. **Perceptible** - Information is easily perceived
5. **Fault-tolerant** - Minimizes errors and consequences

### 2. Keyboard Navigation (Power Users & Accessibility)

**Navigation Patterns:**
```
Tab         - Move forward through interactive elements
Shift+Tab   - Move backward
Enter/Space - Activate buttons, toggles
Escape      - Close modals, cancel actions
Arrow keys  - Navigate lists, menus, sliders
Home/End    - Jump to start/end
```

**Implementation:**
```tsx
// Custom keyboard shortcuts
useEffect(() => {
  const handleKeyDown = (e: KeyboardEvent) => {
    // Cmd+K or Ctrl+K - Open command palette
    if ((e.metaKey || e.ctrlKey) && e.key === 'k') {
      e.preventDefault();
      openCommandPalette();
    }

    // Cmd+N - New task
    if ((e.metaKey || e.ctrlKey) && e.key === 'n') {
      e.preventDefault();
      createTask();
    }
  };

  window.addEventListener('keydown', handleKeyDown);
  return () => window.removeEventListener('keydown', handleKeyDown);
}, []);
```

**Visual Keyboard Shortcut Hints:**
```tsx
<button className="group relative">
  Create Task
  <kbd className="ml-2 px-2 py-1 text-xs bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-800 rounded border border-slate-300 dark:border-slate-600">
    ⌘N
  </kbd>
</button>
```

### 3. Screen Reader Support (Semantic HTML + ARIA)

**Semantic HTML First:**
```tsx
✅ GOOD: Use semantic elements
<nav>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/dashboard">Dashboard</a></li>
    <li><a href="/tasks">Tasks</a></li>
  </ul>
</nav>

❌ BAD: Generic divs
<div>
  <div onClick={goToDashboard}>Dashboard</div>
  <div onClick={goToTasks}>Tasks</div>
</div>
```

**ARIA When Necessary:**
```tsx
// Live regions for dynamic updates
<div
  role="status"
  aria-live="polite"
  aria-atomic="true"
  className="sr-only"
>
  {taskCount} tasks remaining
</div>

// Progress indicators
<div
  role="progressbar"
  aria-valuenow={progress}
  aria-valuemin={0}
  aria-valuemax={100}
  aria-label="Upload progress"
>
  {progress}%
</div>

// Modal dialogs
<div
  role="dialog"
  aria-modal="true"
  aria-labelledby="dialog-title"
  aria-describedby="dialog-description"
>
  <h2 id="dialog-title">Confirm Delete</h2>
  <p id="dialog-description">This action cannot be undone.</p>
</div>
```

### 4. Motion & Animation Accessibility

**Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`:**
```css
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  *,
  *::before,
  *::after {
    animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    animation-iteration-count: 1 !important;
    transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
  }
}
```

**React Implementation:**
```tsx
const prefersReducedMotion = window.matchMedia(
  '(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)'
).matches;

<motion.div
  initial={{ opacity: 0, y: prefersReducedMotion ? 0 : 20 }}
  animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
  transition={{ duration: prefersReducedMotion ? 0 : 0.3 }}
>
  Content
</motion.div>
```

### 5. Color Blindness Considerations

**Don't Rely on Color Alone:**
```tsx
❌ BAD: Color only
<div className="text-red-500">Error</div>
<div className="text-green-500">Success</div>

✅ GOOD: Color + icon + text
<div className="flex items-center gap-2 text-error-500">
  <XCircle className="w-5 h-5" />
  <span className="font-medium">Error:</span> Failed to save
</div>

<div className="flex items-center gap-2 text-success-500">
  <CheckCircle className="w-5 h-5" />
  <span className="font-medium">Success:</span> Saved successfully
</div>
```

**Color Blind Safe Palettes:**
```
Neuman Brain palette is color-blind safe:
- Magenta (#E91E8C) - Distinct hue
- Cyan (#00C9FF) - Distinct hue
- Purple (#9333EA) - Bridge color

Test with: https://www.color-blindness.com/coblis-color-blindness-simulator/
```

