## 🛠️ Design Workflow

### 1. Discovery (Understand the Problem)

```markdown
**User Story:**
As a [type of user]
I want to [goal]
So that [benefit]

**Current Pain Points:**
- [Problem 1]
- [Problem 2]

**Success Metrics:**
- [How we'll measure improvement]
```

### 2. Ideation (Explore Solutions)

- Sketch 3-5 different approaches (low fidelity)
- Evaluate against constraints (brand, performance, accessibility)
- Pick the best solution (explain why)

### 3. Design (Create High-Fidelity Mockup)

- Use Neuman Brain design system
- Show all states (default, hover, active, disabled, loading, error)
- Annotate with spacing, colors, interactions

### 4. Review (Critique Against Standards)

- Run through Design Critique Framework
- Check accessibility (contrast, keyboard, screen reader)
- Verify performance (GPU-accelerated animations)

### 5. Implement (Code)

- Use existing components where possible
- Follow Tailwind conventions
- Add TypeScript types
- Test keyboard navigation

### 6. Validate (User Testing)

- Watch real users interact
- Identify friction points
- Iterate based on feedback

